# YAGOL Brand Assets

Always use these YAGOL brand assets and styling:

## Brand Assets Location
- **Primary Logo:** `assets/logo-full.svg`
- **Icon Logo:** `assets/logo-icon.svg`
- **Favicon:** `assets/favicon.png`

## Brand Colors (Tailwind classes)
- `yagolRed`: #C1272D
- `yagolSilver`: #C0C0C0
- `yagolGold`: #FFD700
- `yagolDark`: #0A0A0A

## Typography
- **Headings:** Montserrat (font-heading class)
- **Body Text:** Lato (font-body class)

## Header Structure
Always use this header structure in HTML files:

```html
<header class="flex justify-between items-center p-4 bg-yagolDark text-white sticky top-0 z-50 shadow-lg">
  <a href="index.html" class="flex items-center gap-2">
    <img src="assets/logo-full.svg" alt="YAGOL Logo" class="h-10 object-contain transition hover:scale-105" />
  </a>
  <nav id="nav-links" class="hidden md:flex space-x-6">
    <a href="index.html" class="hover:text-yagolRed transition">Home</a>
    <a href="about.html" class="hover:text-yagolRed transition">About</a>
    <a href="contact.html" class="hover:text-yagolRed transition">Contact</a>
  </nav>
  
  <!-- Mobile Menu Button -->
  <button id="menu-btn" class="md:hidden text-white">
    <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
      <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M4 6h16M4 12h16M4 18h16"/>
    </svg>
  </button>
  
  <!-- Mobile Navigation -->
  <div id="mobile-nav" class="hidden md:hidden absolute top-full left-0 right-0 bg-yagolDark p-4 shadow-lg">
    <a href="index.html" class="block py-2 hover:text-yagolRed transition">Home</a>
    <a href="about.html" class="block py-2 hover:text-yagolRed transition">About</a>
    <a href="contact.html" class="block py-2 hover:text-yagolRed transition">Contact</a>
  </div>
</header>
```

## Logo Blend Classes
Use these custom classes for proper image blending:
- `logo-blend-dark` - Inverts colors and adds red glow (for dark backgrounds like header)
- `logo-blend-light` - Adds warm sepia/gold tone (for light backgrounds)
- `logo-blend-footer` - Soft blend with sepia/gold for footer dark background
- `logo-blend-hero` - Enhanced glow and brightness for hero sections
- `logo-hover-dark` - Hover effect with enhanced glow for dark backgrounds

## Development Guidelines
- Always use brand colors from the Tailwind config
- Follow the established layout and spacing patterns
- Maintain responsive design (mobile-first)
- Use the custom YAGOL logo assets, not inline SVGs
- Keep header consistent across all pages
- Apply appropriate blend classes to logos for seamless background integration

